and scientifically complex. The dramatic tension of 1960s cinema revolved around the male protagonists’ inability to navigate the challenges of postwar life. Selling over three billion tickets annually, the Soviet film industry became a fault line of postwar cultural contestation. By examining both the discussions surrounding the period’s most controversial movies as well as the cultural context in which these debates happened, the book captures the official and popular reactions to the dizzying transformations of Soviet society after Stalin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aMasculinity in motion pictures. 0aMasculinity in popular culture. 0aMasculinityzSoviet UnionxHistoryy20th century. 0aMen in motion pictures. 0aMen in popular culture. 0aMenzSoviet UnionxIdentityxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszSoviet UnionxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh  a1960s cinema.  aKhrushchev.  aStalin.  ade-Stalinization.  agender studies.  aglobal sixties.  amasculinity and film.  amasculinity crisis.  asoviet film.  asoviet masculinity.  athaw.  aworld cinema.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753184340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487531843423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487531843/original  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL 